author: Kristel Satumbaga
title: Navy sinks Kia spikers
text:
Games Saturday (The Arena, San Juan) 12:45 p.m. – PLDT vs UP 3 p.m. – Coast Guard vs Kia Forte 5 p.m. – Navy vs Army 
Navy combined strong serves with solid defense to score a 25-18, 25-23, 25-21 win over a stubborn Kia Forte side in the Shakey’s V-League Season 12 Reinforced Conference at The Arena in San Juan. 
The Lady Sailors needed one hour and 22 minutes to seal the win, but it was clear they dominated the match – thanks to the inspired plays of Pau Soriano and Pauline Genido. 
While Soriano took charge of the team’s offense, it was Genido who led the team’s defense that helped Navy win its second straight game since dropping its opening game to University of the Philippines. 
Soriano finished with 14 points built around 11 hits while Genido had seven, including four huge blocks. 
The loss was the second straight for Kia. 
Veteran Lilet Mabbayad also shone for the Lady Sailors with nine points, even as Norie Jane Diaz and Therese Veronas chipped in eight and seven points, respectively. 
Janet Serafica was at her usual creative best with 27 excellent sets, while Diaz and Mary Jane Ticar conspired for 17 of the team’s 26 excellent digs. 
Shiela Marie Pineda was the lone double-digit scorer for Kia Forte with 11 points built on eight kills, two blocks and an ace, while Wenneth Eulalio finished with seven points.
